00:18:38.160 --> 00:18:40.479
I think we've had some technical difficulties

00:18:40.479 --> 00:18:42.359
with them coming through Slido.

00:18:42.359 --> 00:18:45.479
So, we're just gonna have to wing some questions.

00:18:45.479 --> 00:18:47.640
So, what's next for Dapr?

00:18:47.640 --> 00:18:49.400
Is it gonna be made public?

00:18:49.400 --> 00:18:52.359
Do you plan to do more than Parquet support?

00:18:52.359 --> 00:18:53.439
What else?

00:18:53.439 --> 00:18:55.160
Yeah, that's a great question.

00:18:55.160 --> 00:18:56.479
So, it is on GitHub.

00:18:56.479 --> 00:18:58.880
We would love to get it on CRAN.

00:18:58.880 --> 00:19:02.000
I would say we're thinking about some refactoring work.

00:19:02.000 --> 00:19:03.959
So, yeah, definitely Parquet development, I think,

00:19:03.959 --> 00:19:06.400
is one of our key first next steps.

00:19:06.400 --> 00:19:07.640
Yeah.

00:19:07.640 --> 00:19:08.680
And then, I'm also curious,

00:19:08.680 --> 00:19:12.560
what was your thought process about deciding to build?

00:19:12.560 --> 00:19:13.560
It does a lot of things,

00:19:13.560 --> 00:19:16.199
but one of the things it does is wrap a bunch of other tools.

00:19:16.199 --> 00:19:18.680
So, what's the trade-off on building another tool

00:19:18.680 --> 00:19:21.400
versus training people on the existing tools?

00:19:22.280 --> 00:19:24.680
Yeah, that's a great question as well.

00:19:24.680 --> 00:19:26.219
It's definitely a trade-off.

00:19:27.479 --> 00:19:29.280
I will say some of these tools

00:19:29.280 --> 00:19:31.000
have a lot of common pain points.

00:19:31.000 --> 00:19:35.239
So, I think the wrapper approach

00:19:35.239 --> 00:19:38.239
forces people to buy into all of the tools at once,

00:19:38.239 --> 00:19:39.520
not just one of them.

00:19:43.280 --> 00:19:45.359
We already had people using the Dapr framework.

00:19:45.359 --> 00:19:47.479
So, as people were interested,

00:19:47.479 --> 00:19:49.920
we could say, hey, learn these reproducible tools

00:19:49.920 --> 00:19:52.359
as you're also learning the framework.

00:19:52.359 --> 00:19:54.239
But it's not always the right,

00:19:54.239 --> 00:19:56.280
Dapr is not always the right solution

00:19:56.280 --> 00:19:57.680
for every analysis question.

00:19:57.680 --> 00:19:59.839
So, it's definitely a trade-off there.

